COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 747, L.D. 1128
1 Sec. 2. Board of Complementary Health Care Providers to adopt rules. No
2 later than January 1, 2026, as authorized by the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 32, section
3 12522, subsection 4, paragraph B, the formulary subcommittee of the Board of
4 Complementary Health Care Providers shall update the formulary for naturopathic doctors
5 and the Board of Complementary Health Care Providers shall adopt the formulary by rule.
6 Prior to making final recommendation to the Board of Complementary Health Care
7 Providers on an update to the formulary, the formulary subcommittee shall consult with
8 pharmacist members of the Maine Board of Pharmacy. Rules adopted by the Board of
9 Complementary Health Care Providers pursuant to this section are major substantive rules
10 as required by Title 32, section 12506.
11 Sec. 3. Authority to report out bill. The Joint Standing Committee on Health
12 Coverage, Insurance and Financial Services may report out a bill to the Second Regular
13 Session of the 132nd Legislature relating to the prescriptive authority of naturopathic
14 doctors.'
15 Amend the bill by adding before the summary the following:
16 'Emergency clause. In view of the emergency cited in the preamble, this legislation
17 takes effect when approved.'
18 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
19 number to read consecutively.
20 SUMMARY
2211 This amendment replaces the bill and adds an emergency preamble and emergency
2222 clause. The amendment corrects an inconsistency in the membership of the formulary
2233 subcommittee of the Board of Complementary Health Care Providers by removing an
2244 outdated reference to a pharmacist member. The amendment requires that the formulary
2255 related to the prescriptive authority of naturopathic doctors must be updated by the
2266 formulary subcommittee of the Board of Complementary Health Care Providers and that
2277 the formulary subcommittee consult with pharmacist members of the Maine Board of
2288 Pharmacy. The amendment requires that the Board of Complementary Health Care
2299 Providers adopt the rule designating the formulary no later than January 1, 2026. The
3300 amendment also authorizes the Joint Standing Committee on Health Coverage, Insurance
3311 and Financial Services to report out a bill relating to the prescriptive authority of
3322 naturopathic doctors to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
3333 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
3344 (See attached)
